{
  "stem": "27507.4",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And there were people who were getting rich as a result of this trade and as a result of connections with the Germans because there-- there were-- there were-- or this were agents of the gestapo who were in the ghetto, who were practically eyes and ears of the Germans.",
      "word_count": 50
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "There were people-- everybody knew that there were people like Kohn and who were kind of ghetto barons who were very rich and were getting richer because they were all the time organizing the trade with the Germans, mainly of the food.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "There was-- and so on and so forth.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "So-- and there was a Pol-- Jewish police who were-- who graduated from relatively doing very-- graduated from cooperating with Germans on the very small scale into cooperating with them on quite a large scale.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "They were-- and one has to say that those-- the Jewish police-- were all from best families.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "They were young-- when they were formed in 1940, they were formed as so-called service of order, [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "Help, you need to carry-- to-- to-- look after order in the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And they were-- in the beginning, it was meant to be a wholly positive element to look that things-- that the law is being more or less kept, et cetera.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And they were to start-- many of them came from so-called good families.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "Many of them were very nice young men.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "They had-- in the beginning, their duties were not in any way horrible.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "They had to do this and that, but-- and they had a uniform.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "They didn't have any weapons.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "They had-- the only weapon they had was a truncheon.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "But and they had their hat, and they were usually dressed quite smartly.",
      "word_count": 13
    }
  ],
